Hi!

I have a short question on the cleaning (memory erasing) of kernel recursive least squares function (krls) in dlib.
I declared klrs function and initialized it.
I trained krls on 100 samples.
I want to train krls on next 100 samples but in a way that previous 100 samples are not impacting the training result of new training iteration.
I tried to use clear_dictionary() but noticed that this doesn't totally clean initially trained krls.
How do you recommend to fully cleaned initially trained krls ??

I'm using the code like

typedef sigmoid_kernel<sample_type> kernel_type;
krls<kernel_type2> krls_predictor(kernel_type(kernel_param, kernel_param2), sensitivity, krls_dictionary_size_);

krls_predictor.clear_dictionary();			
for (int ind = 0; ind < samples.size(); ++ind)
{
	krls_predictor.train(samples[ind], targets[ind]);
	if (krls_predictor.dictionary_size() >= krls_dictionary_size_)
		break;
}

The motivation is setting different error message on SchemaError when trying to validate a single type.

