I'm running into a weird issue where searching a given type of document through `elasticsearch-py` that works ceases to work after I perform a search to a different document type.

I've taken both queries and execute them on ES through kibana and the problem doesn't seem to be happening on ES side I think it's more in the `elasticsearch-py` layer.

I was reading the documentation and it states that there's a connection pool for `urllib3` so instead of instanciating the `Elasticsearch()` client every time I needed I moved it to a shared location for re-use but this proved to be unsuccessful, I'm running out of ideas to debug this issue and it completely breaks my software.

Here's an example of the code I use to search


```
